{"1":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.1","c":"وَالنَّجْمِ","d":"ِmْjgَّnlٱَw","e":"wal-najmi"},{"b":"2.2","h":"2.1","c":"إِذَا","d":"āَhdِiʾ","e":"idhā"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.15","c":"هَوَى","d":"ٰàَwَh","e":"hawā"}],"a":{"g":"By the star when it descends,"}},"2":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.4","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"0.42","h":"0.92","c":"ضَلَّ","d":"َّlَḍ","e":"ḍalla"},{"b":"1.1","h":"1.88","c":"صَاحِبُكُمْ","d":"ْmُkُbِḥāَṣ","e":"ṣāḥibukum"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.96","c":"وَمَا","d":"āَmَw","e":"wamā"},{"b":"3.2","h":"5.07","c":"غَوَى","d":"ٰàَwَغ","e":"ghawā"}],"a":{"g":"Your companion [Muhammad] has not strayed, nor has he erred,"}},"3":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"وَمَا","d":"āَmَw","e":"wamā"},{"b":"0.65","h":"1.4","c":"يَنْطِقُ","d":"ُqِṭnَy","e":"yanṭiqu"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.04","c":"عَنِ","d":"ِnَʿع","e":"ʿani"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.75","c":"الْهَوَى","d":"ٰٓàَwَhْlٱ","e":"l-hawā"}],"a":{"g":"Nor does he speak from [his own] inclination."}},"4":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.15","c":"إِنْ","d":"ْnِiʾ","e":"in"},{"b":"0.43","h":"0.61","c":"هُوَ","d":"َwُh","e":"huwa"},{"b":"0.87","h":"1.24","c":"إِلَّا","d":"āَّlِiʾ","e":"illā"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.52","c":"وَحْيٌ","d":"ٌàْḥَw","e":"waḥyun"},{"b":"3.2","h":"3.53","c":"يُوحَى","d":"ٰàَḥwُy","e":"yūḥā"}],"a":{"g":"It is not but a revelation revealed,"}},"5":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.4","c":"عَلَّمَهُ","d":"ۥُhَmَّlَʿع","e":"ʿallamahu"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.19","c":"شَدِيدُ","d":"ُdyِdَhs","e":"shadīdu"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.62","c":"الْقُوَى","d":"ٰàَwُqْlٱ","e":"l-quwā"}],"a":{"g":"Taught to him by one intense in strength -","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وهو المراد بقوله تعالى علمه شديد القوى ذو مرة فاستوى وهو بالافق الأعلى إلى آخر هذه الآيات وفي مثل هذه الأحوال من الصفاء يقع الاطلاع على ضمائر القلوب وقد يعبر عن ذلك الاطلاع بالتفرس ولذلك قال صلى الله عليه وسلم اتقوا فراسة المؤمن فإنه ينظر بنور الله حديث اتقوا فراسة المؤمن فإنه ينظر بنور الله تعالى أخرجه الترمذي من حديث أبي سعيد وقال حديث غريب وقد حكى أن رجلا من المجوس كان يدور على المسلمين ويقول ما معنى قول النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم اتقوا فراسة المؤمن فكان يذكر له تفسيره فلا يقنعه ذلك حتى انتهى إلى بعض المشايخ من الصوفية فسأله فقال له معناه أن تقطع الزنار الذي على وسطك تحت ثوبك فقال صدقت هذا معناه وأسلم وقال الآن عرفت أنك مؤمن\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, this is what is intended by His, the Exalted's, saying: \"Taught to him by one of intense power [shadid al-quwa], endowed with soundness [dhu mirrah], and he rose [fa-stawa] to his true form at the highest horizon [al-ufuq al-a'la]\" to the end of these verses. And in such states of purity [safa'] occurs the unveiling [al-ittila'] of the innermost secrets [dama'ir] of the hearts [qulub]. And that unveiling [al-ittila'] is sometimes expressed as 'discernment' [al-tafarruṣ]. And for that reason, the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said: \"Be mindful of the discernment [firasah] of the believer, for he sees by the light [nur] of God.\" The hadith \"Be mindful of the discernment [firasah] of the believer, for he sees by the light [nur] of God, the Exalted\" was reported by al-Tirmidhi from the narration of Abu Sa'id, and he said it is a rare [gharib] hadith. And it has been narrated that a man from the Magians [al-Majus] would go around among the Muslims saying, \"What is the meaning of the saying of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, 'Be mindful of the discernment [firasah] of the believer'?\" And its interpretation [tafsir] would be mentioned to him, but that would not satisfy him, until he came to one of the shaykhs from the Sufis [al-Sufiyyah] and asked him. So he said to him, \"Its meaning is that you cut the girdle [al-zunnar] which is around your waist beneath your garment.\" So he said, \"You have spoken the truth. This is its meaning,\" and he embraced Islam, and said, \"Now I have known that you are a believer.\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"6":{"w":[{"b":"0.04","h":"0.25","c":"ذُو","d":"wُhd","e":"dhū"},{"b":"0.54","h":"0.98","c":"مِرَّةٍ","d":"ٍẗَّrِm","e":"mirratin"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.12","c":"فَاسْتَوَى","d":"ٰàَwَtْsٱَf","e":"fa-is'tawā"}],"a":{"g":"One of soundness. And he rose to [his] true form"}},"7":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.23","c":"وَهُوَ","d":"َwُhَw","e":"wahuwa"},{"b":"0.68","h":"1.16","c":"بِالْأُفُقِ","d":"ِqُfُaʾْlٱِb","e":"bil-ufuqi"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.84","c":"الْأَعْلَى","d":"ٰàَlْʿعَaʾْlٱ","e":"l-aʿlā"}],"a":{"g":"While he was in the higher [part of the] horizon."}},"8":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"ثُمَّ","d":"َّmُht","e":"thumma"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.11","c":"دَنَا","d":"āَnَd","e":"danā"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.09","c":"فَتَدَلَّى","d":"ٰàَّlَdَtَf","e":"fatadallā"}],"a":{"g":"Then he approached and descended"}},"9":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"فَكَانَ","d":"َnāَkَf","e":"fakāna"},{"b":"0.9","h":"1.56","c":"قَابَ","d":"َbāَq","e":"qāba"},{"b":"1.5","h":"2.64","c":"قَوْسَيْنِ","d":"ِnْyَsْwَq","e":"qawsayni"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.4","c":"أَوْ","d":"ْwَaʾ","e":"aw"},{"b":"3.2","h":"5.1","c":"أَدْنَى","d":"ٰàَnْdَaʾ","e":"adnā"}],"a":{"g":"And was at a distance of two bow lengths or nearer."}},"10":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"فَأَوْحَى","d":"ٰٓàَḥْwَaʾَf","e":"fa-awḥā"},{"b":"2.4","h":"3.39","c":"إِلَى","d":"ٰàَlِiʾ","e":"ilā"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.29","c":"عَبْدِهِ","d":"ۦِhِdْbَʿع","e":"ʿabdihi"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.16","c":"مَا","d":"ٓāَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"5.9","h":"6.26","c":"أَوْحَى","d":"ٰàَḥْwَaʾ","e":"awḥā"}],"a":{"g":"And he revealed to His Servant what he revealed."}},"11":{"w":[{"b":"0.06","h":"0.35","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"0.47","h":"0.98","c":"كَذَبَ","d":"َbَhdَk","e":"kadhaba"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.02","c":"الْفُؤَادُ","d":"ُdāَwʾُfْlٱ","e":"l-fuādu"},{"b":"2.3","h":"3.88","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.64","c":"رَأَى","d":"ٰٓàَaʾَr","e":"raā"}],"a":{"g":"The heart did not lie [about] what it saw.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                ولموازنة البصيرة الباطنة للبصر الظاهر سماه الله تعالى باسمه فقال ما كذب الفؤاد ما رأى سمى إدراك الفؤاد رؤية\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, to equate the inner insight [al-basirah al-batinah] with the outer sight [al-basr al-zahir], Allah the Exalted named it with His name, saying: \"The heart [al-fu'ad] did not lie about what it saw [ma ra'a].\" He named the perception [idrak] of the heart [al-fu'ad] a seeing [ru'yah].\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"12":{"w":[{"b":"0.07","h":"0.6","c":"أَفَتُمَارُونَهُ","d":"ۥُhَnwُrَٰmُtَfَaʾ","e":"afatumārūnahu"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.78","c":"عَلَى","d":"ٰàَlَʿع","e":"ʿalā"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.9","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"3.5","h":"5.77","c":"يَرَى","d":"ٰàَrَy","e":"yarā"}],"a":{"g":"So will you dispute with him over what he saw?"}},"13":{"w":[{"b":"0.04","h":"0.3","c":"وَلَقَدْ","d":"ْdَqَlَw","e":"walaqad"},{"b":"0.83","h":"1.28","c":"رَءَاهُ","d":"ُhāَءَr","e":"raāhu"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.8","c":"نَزْلَةً","d":"ًẗَlْzَn","e":"nazlatan"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.58","c":"أُخْرَى","d":"ٰàَrْhkُaʾ","e":"ukh'rā"}],"a":{"g":"And he certainly saw him in another descent"}},"14":{"w":[{"b":"0.08","h":"0.35","c":"عِنْدَ","d":"َdnِʿع","e":"ʿinda"},{"b":"1.3","h":"1.53","c":"سِدْرَةِ","d":"ِẗَrْdِs","e":"sid'rati"},{"b":"2.3","h":"2.87","c":"الْمُنْتَهَى","d":"ٰàَhَtnُmْlٱ","e":"l-muntahā"}],"a":{"g":"At the Lote Tree of the Utmost Boundary -"}},"15":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.55","c":"عِنْدَهَا","d":"āَhَdnِʿع","e":"ʿindahā"},{"b":"1.9","h":"2.66","c":"جَنَّةُ","d":"ُẗَّnَjg","e":"jannatu"},{"b":"3.6","h":"4.41","c":"الْمَأْوَى","d":"ٰٓàَwْaʾَmْlٱ","e":"l-mawā"}],"a":{"g":"Near it is the Garden of Refuge -"}},"16":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"إِذْ","d":"ْhdِiʾ","e":"idh"},{"b":"0.39","h":"1.31","c":"يَغْشَى","d":"àَhsْغَy","e":"yaghshā"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.32","c":"السِّدْرَةَ","d":"َẗَrْdِّslٱ","e":"l-sid'rata"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.99","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.8","c":"يَغْشَى","d":"ٰàَhsْغَy","e":"yaghshā"}],"a":{"g":"When there covered the Lote Tree that which covered [it]."}},"17":{"w":[{"b":"0.05","h":"0.4","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"0.47","h":"0.96","c":"زَاغَ","d":"َغāَz","e":"zāgha"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.14","c":"الْبَصَرُ","d":"ُrَṣَbْlٱ","e":"l-baṣaru"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.59","c":"وَمَا","d":"āَmَw","e":"wamā"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.6","c":"طَغَى","d":"ٰàَغَṭ","e":"ṭaghā"}],"a":{"g":"The sight [of the Prophet] did not swerve, nor did it transgress [its limit]."}},"18":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.15","c":"لَقَدْ","d":"ْdَqَl","e":"laqad"},{"b":"0.62","h":"0.86","c":"رَأَى","d":"ٰàَaʾَr","e":"raā"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.06","c":"مِنْ","d":"ْnِm","e":"min"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.79","c":"ءَايَاتِ","d":"ِtَٰyāَء","e":"āyāti"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.66","c":"رَبِّهِ","d":"ِhِّbَr","e":"rabbihi"},{"b":"3.9","h":"6.16","c":"الْكُبْرَى","d":"ٰٓàَrْbُkْlٱ","e":"l-kub'rā"}],"a":{"g":"He certainly saw of the greatest signs of his Lord."}},"19":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"أَفَرَءَيْتُمُ","d":"ُmُtْyَءَrَfَaʾ","e":"afara-aytumu"},{"b":"1.6","h":"2.85","c":"اللَّاتَ","d":"َtَّٰllٱ","e":"l-lāta"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.26","c":"وَالْعُزَّى","d":"ٰàَّzُʿعْlٱَw","e":"wal-ʿuzā"}],"a":{"g":"So have you considered al-Lat and al-'Uzza?"}},"20":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.2","c":"وَمَنَوةَ","d":"َẗٰwَnَmَw","e":"wamanata"},{"b":"1.1","h":"1.73","c":"الثَّالِثَةَ","d":"َẗَhtِlāَّhtlٱ","e":"l-thālithata"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.8","c":"الْأُخْرَى","d":"ٰٓàَrْhkُaʾْlٱ","e":"l-ukh'rā"}],"a":{"g":"And Manat, the third - the other one?"}},"21":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"أَلَكُمُ","d":"ُmُkَlَaʾ","e":"alakumu"},{"b":"0.88","h":"2.09","c":"الذَّكَرُ","d":"ُrَkَّhdlٱ","e":"l-dhakaru"},{"b":"1.8","h":"3.13","c":"وَلَهُ","d":"ُhَlَw","e":"walahu"},{"b":"2.5","h":"4.14","c":"الْأُنْثَى","d":"ٰàَhtnُaʾْlٱ","e":"l-unthā"}],"a":{"g":"Is the male for you and for Him the female?"}},"22":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"تِلْكَ","d":"َkْlِt","e":"til'ka"},{"b":"0.62","h":"1.3","c":"إِذًا","d":"āًhdِiʾ","e":"idhan"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.61","c":"قِسْمَةٌ","d":"ٌẗَmْsِq","e":"qis'matun"},{"b":"4.4","h":"4.89","c":"ضِيزَى","d":"ٰٓàَzyِḍ","e":"ḍīzā"}],"a":{"g":"That, then, is an unjust division."}},"23":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.03","c":"إِنْ","d":"ْnِiʾ","e":"in"},{"b":"0.44","h":"0.69","c":"هِيَ","d":"َàِh","e":"hiya"},{"b":"0.89","h":"1.38","c":"إِلَّا","d":"ٓāَّlِiʾ","e":"illā"},{"b":"2.8","h":"3.66","c":"أَسْمَاءٌ","d":"ٌءٓāَmْsَaʾ","e":"asmāon"},{"b":"6.4","h":"7.04","c":"سَمَّيْتُمُوهَا","d":"ٓāَhwُmُtْyَّmَs","e":"sammaytumūhā"},{"b":"13.0","h":"10.02","c":"أَنْتُمْ","d":"ْmُtnَaʾ","e":"antum"},{"b":"15.8","h":"13.54","c":"وَءَابَاؤُكُمْ","d":"mُkُwʾٓāَbāَءَw","e":"waābāukum"},{"b":"19.8","h":"17.38","c":"مَا","d":"ٓāَّm","e":"mā"},{"b":"19.8","h":"17.76","c":"أَنْزَلَ","d":"َlَznَaʾ","e":"anzala"},{"b":"22.8","h":"20.88","c":"اللَّهُ","d":"ُhَّllٱ","e":"l-lahu"},{"b":"23.8","h":"22.36","c":"بِهَا","d":"āَhِb","e":"bihā"},{"b":"24.5","h":"23.42","c":"مِنْ","d":"nِm","e":"min"},{"b":"25.7","h":"24.5","c":"سُلْطَانٍ","d":"ٍnَٰṭْlُs","e":"sul'ṭānin"},{"b":"29.","h":"31.4","c":"إِنْ","d":"nِiʾ","e":"in"},{"b":"30.3","h":"32.42","c":"يَتَّبِعُونَ","d":"َnwُʿعِbَّtَy","e":"yattabiʿūna"},{"b":"31.","h":"34.68","c":"إِلَّا","d":"āَّlِiʾ","e":"illā"},{"b":"32.5","h":"35.6","c":"الظَّنَّ","d":"َّnَّẓlٱ","e":"l-ẓana"},{"b":"34.1","h":"37.44","c":"وَمَا","d":"āَmَw","e":"wamā"},{"b":"34.7","h":"38.48","c":"تَهْوَى","d":"àَwْhَt","e":"tahwā"},{"b":"35.5","h":"39.61","c":"الْأَنْفُسُ","d":"ُsُfnَaʾْlٱ","e":"l-anfusu"},{"b":"38.3","h":"43.25","c":"وَلَقَدْ","d":"ْdَqَlَw","e":"walaqad"},{"b":"39.1","h":"44.49","c":"جَاءَهُمْ","d":"mُhَءٓāَjg","e":"jāahum"},{"b":"42.9","h":"47.68","c":"مِنْ","d":"nِّm","e":"min"},{"b":"43.1","h":"47.87","c":"رَبِّهِمُ","d":"ُmِhِّbَّr","e":"rabbihimu"},{"b":"44.5","h":"50.2","c":"الْهُدَى","d":"ٰٓàَdُhْlٱ","e":"l-hudā"}],"a":{"g":"They are not but [mere] names you have named them - you and your forefathers - for which Allah has sent down no authority. They follow not except assumption and what [their] souls desire, and there has already come to them from their Lord guidance."}},"24":{"w":[{"b":"0.04","h":"0.55","c":"أَمْ","d":"ْmَaʾ","e":"am"},{"b":"0.4","h":"1.1","c":"لِلْإِنْسَانِ","d":"ِnَٰsnِiʾْlِl","e":"lil'insāni"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.02","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"3.2","h":"4.72","c":"تَمَنَّى","d":"ٰàَّnَmَt","e":"tamannā"}],"a":{"g":"Or is there for man whatever he wishes?"}},"25":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"فَلِلَّهِ","d":"ِhَّlِlَf","e":"falillahi"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.22","c":"الْءَاخِرَةُ","d":"ُẗَrِhkāَءْlٱ","e":"l-ākhiratu"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.32","c":"وَالْأُولَى","d":"ٰàَlwُaʾْlٱَw","e":"wal-ūlā"}],"a":{"g":"Rather, to Allah belongs the Hereafter and the first [life]."}},"26":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.79","c":"وَكَمْ","d":"mَkَw","e":"wakam"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.57","c":"مِنْ","d":"nِّm","e":"min"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.69","c":"مَلَكٍ","d":"ٍkَlَّm","e":"malakin"},{"b":"3.9","h":"5.37","c":"فِي","d":"àِf","e":"fī"},{"b":"4.2","h":"5.74","c":"السَّمَاوَاتِ","d":"ِtَٰwَٰmَّslٱ","e":"l-samāwāti"},{"b":"5.9","h":"8.2","c":"لَا","d":"āَl","e":"lā"},{"b":"6.2","h":"8.8","c":"تُغْنِي","d":"àِnْغُt","e":"tugh'nī"},{"b":"7.1","h":"10.12","c":"شَفَاعَتُهُمْ","d":"ْmُhُtَʿعَٰfَhs","e":"shafāʿatuhum"},{"b":"8.8","h":"12.74","c":"شَيْئًا","d":"āًٔـْyَhs","e":"shayan"},{"b":"14.","h":"13.25","c":"إِلَّا","d":"āَّlِiʾ","e":"illā"},{"b":"15.2","h":"13.89","c":"مِنْ","d":"ۢnِm","e":"min"},{"b":"16.5","h":"16.75","c":"بَعْدِ","d":"ِdْʿعَb","e":"baʿdi"},{"b":"17.2","h":"17.91","c":"أَنْ","d":"nَaʾ","e":"an"},{"b":"18.2","h":"19.03","c":"يَأْذَنَ","d":"َnَhdْaʾَy","e":"yadhana"},{"b":"19.0","h":"20.29","c":"اللَّهُ","d":"ُhَّllٱ","e":"l-lahu"},{"b":"20.0","h":"21.76","c":"لِمَنْ","d":"nَmِl","e":"liman"},{"b":"21.1","h":"23.3","c":"يَشَاءُ","d":"ُءٓāَhsَy","e":"yashāu"},{"b":"23.4","h":"25.71","c":"وَيَرْضَى","d":"ٰٓàَḍْrَyَw","e":"wayarḍā"}],"a":{"g":"And how many angels there are in the heavens whose intercession will not avail at all except [only] after Allah has permitted [it] to whom He wills and approves."}},"27":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.9","c":"إِنَّ","d":"َّnِiʾ","e":"inna"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.17","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"َnyِhdَّlٱ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.89","c":"لَا","d":"āَl","e":"lā"},{"b":"3.3","h":"4.57","c":"يُؤْمِنُونَ","d":"َnwُnِmْwʾُy","e":"yu'minūna"},{"b":"4.7","h":"6.54","c":"بِالْءَاخِرَةِ","d":"ِẗَrِhkāَءْlٱِb","e":"bil-ākhirati"},{"b":"6.3","h":"8.91","c":"لَيُسَمُّونَ","d":"َnwُّmَsُyَl","e":"layusammūna"},{"b":"8.7","h":"11.57","c":"الْمَلَائِكَةَ","d":"َẗَkِyʾَٰٓlَmْlٱ","e":"l-malāikata"},{"b":"11.8","h":"14.73","c":"تَسْمِيَةَ","d":"َẗَyِmْsَt","e":"tasmiyata"},{"b":"12.9","h":"16.61","c":"الْأُنْثَى","d":"ٰàَhtnُaʾْlٱ","e":"l-unthā"}],"a":{"g":"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter name the angels female names,"}},"28":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.87","c":"وَمَا","d":"āَmَw","e":"wamā"},{"b":"0.66","h":"1.83","c":"لَهُمْ","d":"mُhَl","e":"lahum"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.19","c":"بِهِ","d":"ۦِhِb","e":"bihi"},{"b":"2.9","h":"4.28","c":"مِنْ","d":"ْnِm","e":"min"},{"b":"3.3","h":"4.84","c":"عِلْمٍ","d":"ٍmْlِʿع","e":"ʿil'min"},{"b":"4.4","h":"6.34","c":"إِنْ","d":"nِiʾ","e":"in"},{"b":"5.8","h":"7.39","c":"يَتَّبِعُونَ","d":"َnwُʿعِbَّtَy","e":"yattabiʿūna"},{"b":"7.2","h":"9.69","c":"إِلَّا","d":"āَّlِiʾ","e":"illā"},{"b":"7.8","h":"10.74","c":"الظَّنَّ","d":"َّnَّẓlٱ","e":"l-ẓana"},{"b":"9.5","h":"13.85","c":"وَإِنَّ","d":"َّnِiʾَw","e":"wa-inna"},{"b":"10.9","h":"15.49","c":"الظَّنَّ","d":"َّnَّẓlٱ","e":"l-ẓana"},{"b":"12.3","h":"17.32","c":"لَا","d":"āَl","e":"lā"},{"b":"12.7","h":"17.98","c":"يُغْنِي","d":"àِnْغُy","e":"yugh'nī"},{"b":"13.7","h":"19.49","c":"مِنَ","d":"َnِm","e":"mina"},{"b":"14.1","h":"20.05","c":"الْحَقِّ","d":"ِّqَḥْlٱ","e":"l-ḥaqi"},{"b":"15.0","h":"21.43","c":"شَيْئًا","d":"āًٔـْyَhs","e":"shayan"}],"a":{"g":"And they have thereof no knowledge. They follow not except assumption, and indeed, assumption avails not against the truth at all."}},"29":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.75","c":"فَأَعْرِضْ","d":"ْḍِrْʿعَaʾَf","e":"fa-aʿriḍ"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.17","c":"عَنْ","d":"nَʿع","e":"ʿan"},{"b":"2.0","h":"3.39","c":"مَنْ","d":"nَّm","e":"man"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.37","c":"تَوَلَّى","d":"ٰàَّlَwَt","e":"tawallā"},{"b":"3.9","h":"6.33","c":"عَنْ","d":"nَʿع","e":"ʿan"},{"b":"5.0","h":"7.44","c":"ذِكْرِنَا","d":"āَnِrْkِhd","e":"dhik'rinā"},{"b":"6.1","h":"9.25","c":"وَلَمْ","d":"ْmَlَw","e":"walam"},{"b":"6.8","h":"10.1","c":"يُرِدْ","d":"ْdِrُy","e":"yurid"},{"b":"7.5","h":"11.19","c":"إِلَّا","d":"āَّlِiʾ","e":"illā"},{"b":"8.1","h":"12.15","c":"الْحَيَوةَ","d":"َẗٰwَyَḥْlٱ","e":"l-ḥayata"},{"b":"9.3","h":"14","c":"الدُّنْيَا","d":"āَyْnُّdlٱ","e":"l-dun'yā"}],"a":{"g":"So turn away from whoever turns his back on Our message and desires not except the worldly life.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                ولما انكشف لأولياء الله تعالى أن العبد مهلك نفسه بأعماله واتباعه هوى نفسه إهلاك دود القز نفسه: رفضوا الدنيا بالكلية، حتى قال الحسن: رأيت سبعين بدرياً كانوا فيما أحل الله لهم أزهد منكم فيما حرم الله عليكم. وفي لفظ آخر: كانوا بالبلاء أشد قرحاً منكم بالخصب والرخاء لو رأيتموهم قلتم مجانين، ولو رأوا خياركم قالوا ما لهؤلاء من خلاق، ولو رأوا أشراركم قالوا ما يؤمن هؤلاء بيوم الحساب. وكان أحدهم يعرض لهم المال الحلال فلا يأخذه ويقول: أخاف أن يفسد على قلبي، فمن كان له قلب فهو لا محالة يخاف من فساده، والذين أمات حب الدنيا قلوبهم فقد أخبر الله عنهم إذ قال تعالى: \" فأعرض عمن تولى عن ذكرنا ولم يرد إلا الحياة الدنيا، ذلك مبلغهم من العلم\"، فأحال ذلك كله على الغفلة وعدم العلم.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, when it was unveiled [inkashafa] for the friends [awliya'] of God, the Exalted, that the servant destroys his own soul [nafs] by his actions and his following of his soul's [nafs] desire [hawa]—like the silkworm destroying itself—they rejected the world [dunya] completely. So much so that Al-Hasan said: \"I saw seventy of the Companions of Badr; they were, in what God had made lawful for them, more abstinent than you are in what God has forbidden for you.\" And in another wording: \"They were in hardship more wounded than you are in ease and plenty. If you saw them, you would say, 'They are madmen,' and if they saw the best of you, they would say, 'These have no share [khalāq],' and if they saw the worst of you, they would say, 'These do not believe in the Day of Reckoning.'\" And one of them would be offered lawful wealth and would not take it, saying, \"I fear it will corrupt my heart [qalb].\" For whoever possesses a heart [qalb] inevitably fears its corruption. And those whose hearts [qulub] have been killed by the love of the world [dunya]—God has informed about them when He, the Exalted, said: \"So turn away from him who turns away from Our Remembrance and desires nothing but the life of this world [dunya]. That is the extent of their knowledge ['ilm].\" He attributed all of that to heedlessness [ghafla] and the absence of knowledge ['ilm].\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"30":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"ذَلِكَ","d":"َkِlَٰhd","e":"dhālika"},{"b":"0.89","h":"1.98","c":"مَبْلَغُهُمْ","d":"mُhُغَlْbَm","e":"mablaghuhum"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.33","c":"مِنَ","d":"َnِّm","e":"mina"},{"b":"3.3","h":"5.22","c":"الْعِلْمِ","d":"ِmْlِʿعْlٱ","e":"l-ʿil'mi"},{"b":"4.6","h":"7.95","c":"إِنَّ","d":"َّnِiʾ","e":"inna"},{"b":"5.7","h":"8.98","c":"رَبَّكَ","d":"َkَّbَr","e":"rabbaka"},{"b":"6.5","h":"10.42","c":"هُوَ","d":"َwُh","e":"huwa"},{"b":"7.0","h":"11.13","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"ُmَlْʿعَaʾ","e":"aʿlamu"},{"b":"7.9","h":"12.58","c":"بِمَنْ","d":"nَmِb","e":"biman"},{"b":"9.2","h":"14","c":"ضَلَّ","d":"َّlَḍ","e":"ḍalla"},{"b":"9.8","h":"14.8","c":"عَنْ","d":"nَʿع","e":"ʿan"},{"b":"10.7","h":"15.9","c":"سَبِيلِهِ","d":"ۦِhِlyِbَs","e":"sabīlihi"},{"b":"12.1","h":"18.19","c":"وَهُوَ","d":"َwُhَw","e":"wahuwa"},{"b":"12.8","h":"19.15","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"ُmَlْʿعَaʾ","e":"aʿlamu"},{"b":"13.7","h":"20.59","c":"بِمَنِ","d":"ِnَmِb","e":"bimani"},{"b":"14.3","h":"21.57","c":"اهْتَدَى","d":"ٰàَdَtْhٱ","e":"ih'tadā"}],"a":{"g":"That is their sum of knowledge. Indeed, your Lord is most knowing of who strays from His way, and He is most knowing of who is guided."}},"31":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.47","c":"وَلِلَّهِ","d":"ِhَّlِlَw","e":"walillahi"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.18","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.83","c":"فِي","d":"àِf","e":"fī"},{"b":"2.0","h":"3.17","c":"السَّمَاوَاتِ","d":"ِtَٰwَٰmَّslٱ","e":"l-samāwāti"},{"b":"3.6","h":"5.58","c":"وَمَا","d":"āَmَw","e":"wamā"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.59","c":"فِي","d":"àِf","e":"fī"},{"b":"4.6","h":"7.06","c":"الْأَرْضِ","d":"ِḍْrَaʾْlٱ","e":"l-arḍi"},{"b":"5.5","h":"10.05","c":"لِيَجْزِيَ","d":"َàِzْjgَyِl","e":"liyajziya"},{"b":"6.7","h":"11.49","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"َnyِhdَّlٱ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"7.8","h":"13.12","c":"أَسَاءُوا","d":"۟āwُٔـَٰٓsَaʾ","e":"asāū"},{"b":"10.8","h":"15.69","c":"بِمَا","d":"āَmِb","e":"bimā"},{"b":"11.4","h":"16.5","c":"عَمِلُوا","d":"۟āwُlِmَʿع","e":"ʿamilū"},{"b":"12.5","h":"18.1","c":"وَيَجْزِيَ","d":"َàِzْjgَyَw","e":"wayajziya"},{"b":"13.5","h":"19.55","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"َnyِhdَّlٱ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"14.7","h":"21.23","c":"أَحْسَنُوا","d":"۟āwُnَsْḥَaʾ","e":"aḥsanū"},{"b":"15.8","h":"22.92","c":"بِالْحُسْنَى","d":"àَnْsُḥْlٱِb","e":"bil-ḥus'nā"}],"a":{"g":"And to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth - that He may recompense those who do evil with [the penalty of] what they have done and recompense those who do good with the best [reward] -","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                هنالك تجزى كل نفس بما كسبت إن الله عز وجل يقول \"ليجزى الذي أساءوا بما عملوا ويجزى الذي أحسنوا بالحسنى\"\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, there, every soul [nafs] will be recompensed for what it has earned. Indeed, Allah, the Mighty and Majestic, says: \"That He may recompense those who did evil for what they did, and recompense those who did good with the best [al-husna].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"32":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.75","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"َnyِhdَّlٱ","e":"alladhīna"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.47","c":"يَجْتَنِبُونَ","d":"َnwُbِnَtْjgَy","e":"yajtanibūna"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.77","c":"كَبَائِرَ","d":"َrِyʾَٰٓbَk","e":"kabāira"},{"b":"5.5","h":"7.11","c":"الْإِثْمِ","d":"ِmْhtِiʾْlٱ","e":"l-ith'mi"},{"b":"6.4","h":"8.37","c":"وَالْفَوَاحِشَ","d":"َhsِḥَٰwَfْlٱَw","e":"wal-fawāḥisha"},{"b":"8.0","h":"10.76","c":"إِلَّا","d":"āَّlِiʾ","e":"illā"},{"b":"8.7","h":"11.7","c":"اللَّمَمَ","d":"َmَmَّllٱ","e":"l-lamama"},{"b":"10.1","h":"16","c":"إِنَّ","d":"َّnِiʾ","e":"inna"},{"b":"11.4","h":"17.3","c":"رَبَّكَ","d":"َkَّbَr","e":"rabbaka"},{"b":"12.3","h":"18.7","c":"وَاسِعُ","d":"ُʿعِsَٰw","e":"wāsiʿu"},{"b":"13.2","h":"20.15","c":"الْمَغْفِرَةِ","d":"ِẗَrِfْغَmْlٱ","e":"l-maghfirati"},{"b":"15.1","h":"24.15","c":"هُوَ","d":"َwُh","e":"huwa"},{"b":"15.5","h":"24.66","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"ُmَlْʿعَaʾ","e":"aʿlamu"},{"b":"16.3","h":"25.94","c":"بِكُمْ","d":"ْmُkِb","e":"bikum"},{"b":"17.0","h":"26.9","c":"إِذْ","d":"ْhdِiʾ","e":"idh"},{"b":"17.","h":"27.43","c":"أَنْشَأَكُمْ","d":"mُkَaʾَhsnَaʾ","e":"ansha-akum"},{"b":"20.0","h":"30.43","c":"مِنَ","d":"َnِّm","e":"mina"},{"b":"20.3","h":"30.93","c":"الْأَرْضِ","d":"ِḍْrَaʾْlٱ","e":"l-arḍi"},{"b":"21.3","h":"32.23","c":"وَإِذْ","d":"ْhdِiʾَw","e":"wa-idh"},{"b":"21.9","h":"33.13","c":"أَنْتُمْ","d":"ْmُtnَaʾ","e":"antum"},{"b":"23.5","h":"35.13","c":"أَجِنَّةٌ","d":"ٌẗَّnِjgَaʾ","e":"ajinnatun"},{"b":"25.9","h":"37.74","c":"فِي","d":"àِf","e":"fī"},{"b":"26.4","h":"38.53","c":"بُطُونِ","d":"ِnwُṭُb","e":"buṭūni"},{"b":"27.4","h":"40.89","c":"أُمَّهَاتِكُمْ","d":"ْmُkِtَٰhَّmُaʾ","e":"ummahātikum"},{"b":"30.5","h":"46.4","c":"فَلَا","d":"āَlَf","e":"falā"},{"b":"31.1","h":"47.22","c":"تُزَكُّوا","d":"۟āٓwُّkَzُt","e":"tuzakkū"},{"b":"34.1","h":"50.09","c":"أَنْفُسَكُمْ","d":"ْmُkَsُfnَaʾ","e":"anfusakum"},{"b":"36.","h":"54.5","c":"هُوَ","d":"َwُh","e":"huwa"},{"b":"37.","h":"54.97","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"ُmَlْʿعَaʾ","e":"aʿlamu"},{"b":"37.9","h":"56.24","c":"بِمَنِ","d":"ِnَmِb","e":"bimani"},{"b":"38.6","h":"57.11","c":"اتَّقَى","d":"ٰٓàَqَّtٱ","e":"ittaqā"}],"a":{"g":"Those who avoid the major sins and immoralities, only [committing] slight ones. Indeed, your Lord is vast in forgiveness. He was most knowing of you when He produced you from the earth and when you were fetuses in the wombs of your mothers. So do not claim yourselves to be pure; He is most knowing of who fears Him.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                بيان ذم العجب وآفاته اعلم أن العجب مذموم في كتاب الله تعالى وسنة رسوله ﭬ. وقد قال تعالى: \"فلا تزكوا أنفسكم\" قال ابن جريج: معناه إذا عملت خيراً فلا تقل عملت. وقال زيد بن أسلم. لا تبروها، أي لا تعتقدوا أنها بارة وهو معنى العجب. وقد قال تعالى \"لا تبطلوا صدقاتكم بالمن والأذى\" والمن نتيجة استعظام الصدقة، واستعظام العمل هو العجب. فظهر بهذا أن العجب مذموم جداً.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, the explanation of the censure of self-admiration [al-'ujb] and its destructive consequences. Know that self-admiration [al-'ujb] is censured in the Book of Allah, the Most High, and the Sunnah of His Messenger, peace be upon him. And He, the Most High, has said: \"So do not claim purity for yourselves [fa la tuzakku anfusakum].\" Ibn Jurayj said: Its meaning is, when you perform a good deed, do not say, 'I performed it.' And Zayd ibn Aslam said: Do not declare them righteous, meaning do not believe they are righteous, and this is the meaning of self-admiration [al-'ujb]. And He, the Most High, has said: \"Do not invalidate your charities with reminders of your generosity [al-mann] or injury.\" And the reminder of generosity [al-mann] is the result of magnifying the charity, and magnifying the deed is self-admiration [al-'ujb]. Thus, it becomes clear by this that self-admiration [al-'ujb] is most severely censured.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"33":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.55","c":"أَفَرَءَيْتَ","d":"َtْyَءَrَfَaʾ","e":"afara-ayta"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.25","c":"الَّذِي","d":"àِhdَّlٱ","e":"alladhī"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.52","c":"تَوَلَّى","d":"ٰàَّlَwَt","e":"tawallā"}],"a":{"g":"Have you seen the one who turned away"}},"34":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"وَأَعْطَى","d":"ٰàَṭْʿعَaʾَw","e":"wa-aʿṭā"},{"b":"1.0","h":"1.9","c":"قَلِيلًا","d":"āًlyِlَq","e":"qalīlan"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.34","c":"وَأَكْدَى","d":"ٰٓàَdْkَaʾَw","e":"wa-akdā"}],"a":{"g":"And gave a little and [then] refrained?"}},"35":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"أَعِنْدَهُ","d":"ۥُhَdnِʿعَaʾ","e":"aʿindahu"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.47","c":"عِلْمُ","d":"ُmْlِʿع","e":"ʿil'mu"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.52","c":"الْغَيْبِ","d":"ِbْyَغْlٱ","e":"l-ghaybi"},{"b":"3.3","h":"4.92","c":"فَهُوَ","d":"َwُhَf","e":"fahuwa"},{"b":"4.0","h":"6","c":"يَرَى","d":"ٰٓàَrَy","e":"yarā"}],"a":{"g":"Does he have knowledge of the unseen, so he sees?"}},"36":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1.15","c":"أَمْ","d":"ْmَaʾ","e":"am"},{"b":"0.38","h":"1.59","c":"لَمْ","d":"ْmَl","e":"lam"},{"b":"0.79","h":"2.16","c":"يُنَبَّأْ","d":"ْaʾَّbَnُy","e":"yunabba"},{"b":"1.7","h":"3.74","c":"بِمَا","d":"āَmِb","e":"bimā"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.79","c":"فِي","d":"àِf","e":"fī"},{"b":"2.9","h":"5.53","c":"صُحُفِ","d":"ِfُḥُṣ","e":"ṣuḥufi"},{"b":"3.6","h":"6.61","c":"مُوسَى","d":"ٰàَswُm","e":"mūsā"}],"a":{"g":"Or has he not been informed of what was in the scriptures of Moses","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال زياد خلوا سبيله، هذا رجل قد لقن حجته.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                And Ziyad said, \"Leave his way, for this is a man whose argument has been instilled [luqqina hujjatuhu].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"37":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1","c":"وَإِبْرَاهِيمَ","d":"َmyِhَٰrْbِiʾَw","e":"wa-ib'rāhīma"},{"b":"1.6","h":"3.42","c":"الَّذِي","d":"àِhdَّlٱ","e":"alladhī"},{"b":"2.5","h":"4.83","c":"وَفَّى","d":"ٰٓàَّfَw","e":"waffā"}],"a":{"g":"And [of] Abraham, who fulfilled [his obligations] -","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وروي أنه لما قال جبريل لإبراهيم عليهما السلام وقد رمي إلى النار بالمنجنيق: ألك حاجة؟ قال: أما إليك فلا، وفاءً بقوله حسبي الله ونعم الوكيل، إذا قال ذلك حين أخذ ليرمى، فأنزل الله تعالى: \" وإبراهيم الذي وفى \".\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, it is narrated that when Gabriel [Jibril], peace be upon them both, said to Abraham [Ibrahim] as he was catapulted into the fire, \"Do you have any need?\" he replied, \"Not from you,\" fulfilling his statement, \"Sufficient for me is Allah [Allah], and He is the best Disposer of affairs [al-Wakil],\" which he had said when he was taken to be thrown. Then Allah, the Exalted, revealed: \"And [of] Abraham who fulfilled [wa-Ibrahim alladhi waffa].\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"38":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.65","c":"أَلَّا","d":"āَّlَaʾ","e":"allā"},{"b":"0.8","h":"1.84","c":"تَزِرُ","d":"ُrِzَt","e":"taziru"},{"b":"1.5","h":"2.97","c":"وَازِرَةٌ","d":"ٌẗَrِzāَw","e":"wāziratun"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.35","c":"وِزْرَ","d":"َrْzِw","e":"wiz'ra"},{"b":"4.1","h":"6.33","c":"أُخْرَى","d":"ٰàَrْhkُaʾ","e":"ukh'rā"}],"a":{"g":"That no bearer of burdens will bear the burden of another"}},"39":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"وَأَنْ","d":"nَaʾَw","e":"wa-an"},{"b":"0.33","h":"1.33","c":"لَيْسَ","d":"َsْyَّl","e":"laysa"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.74","c":"لِلْإِنْسَانِ","d":"ِnَٰsnِiʾْlِl","e":"lil'insāni"},{"b":"3.6","h":"5.64","c":"إِلَّا","d":"āَّlِiʾ","e":"illā"},{"b":"4.5","h":"7.03","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"4.8","h":"7.83","c":"سَعَى","d":"ٰàَʿعَs","e":"saʿā"}],"a":{"g":"And that there is not for man except that [good] for which he strives","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال في أمر الآخرة وأن ليس للإنسان إلا ما سعى فقد تكفل لك بأمر الدنيا خاصة وصرفك عن السعى فيها فكذبته بأفعالك وأصبحت تتكالبين على طلبها تكالب المدهوش المستهتر ووكل أمر الآخرة إلى سعيك فأعرضت عنها إعراض المغرور المستحقر.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, concerning the matter of the Hereafter [al-akhirah] and that for man there is only what he strives for, He has guaranteed for you the matter of the world [al-dunya] specifically and diverted you from striving in it. Yet you have belied Him with your actions, and you have become one who scrambles in pursuit of it, scrambling like one who is bewildered and heedless. And He has entrusted the matter of the Hereafter [al-akhirah] to your striving, yet you have turned away from it, turning away like one who is deluded and contemptuous.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"40":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"وَأَنَّ","d":"َّnَaʾَw","e":"wa-anna"},{"b":"1.2","h":"2.28","c":"سَعْيَهُ","d":"ۥُhَyْʿعَs","e":"saʿyahu"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.09","c":"سَوْفَ","d":"َfْwَs","e":"sawfa"},{"b":"3.0","h":"5.2","c":"يُرَى","d":"ٰàَrُy","e":"yurā"}],"a":{"g":"And that his effort is going to be seen -"}},"41":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"ثُمَّ","d":"َّmُht","e":"thumma"},{"b":"1.0","h":"1.61","c":"يُجْزَاهُ","d":"ُhٰàَzْjgُy","e":"yuj'zāhu"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.3","c":"الْجَزَاءَ","d":"َءٓāَzَjgْlٱ","e":"l-jazāa"},{"b":"4.7","h":"5.87","c":"الْأَوْفَى","d":"ٰàَfْwَaʾْlٱ","e":"l-awfā"}],"a":{"g":"Then he will be recompensed for it with the fullest recompense"}},"42":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.61","c":"وَأَنَّ","d":"َّnَaʾَw","e":"wa-anna"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.02","c":"إِلَى","d":"ٰàَlِiʾ","e":"ilā"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.06","c":"رَبِّكَ","d":"َkِّbَr","e":"rabbika"},{"b":"3.0","h":"4.68","c":"الْمُنْتَهَى","d":"ٰàَhَtnُmْlٱ","e":"l-muntahā"}],"a":{"g":"And that to your Lord is the finality"}},"43":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"ۥُhَّnَaʾَw","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.64","c":"هُوَ","d":"َwُh","e":"huwa"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.33","c":"أَضْحَكَ","d":"َkَḥْḍَaʾ","e":"aḍḥaka"},{"b":"3.1","h":"4.82","c":"وَأَبْكَى","d":"ٰàَkْbَaʾَw","e":"wa-abkā"}],"a":{"g":"And that it is He who makes [one] laugh and weep"}},"44":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.65","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"ۥُhَّnَaʾَw","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"1.9","h":"2.78","c":"هُوَ","d":"َwُh","e":"huwa"},{"b":"2.2","h":"3.5","c":"أَمَاتَ","d":"َtāَmَaʾ","e":"amāta"},{"b":"3.2","h":"4.98","c":"وَأَحْيَا","d":"āَyْḥَaʾَw","e":"wa-aḥyā"}],"a":{"g":"And that it is He who causes death and gives life"}},"45":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.6","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"ۥُhَّnَaʾَw","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.82","c":"خَلَقَ","d":"َqَlَhk","e":"khalaqa"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.9","c":"الزَّوْجَيْنِ","d":"ِnْyَjgْwَّzlٱ","e":"l-zawjayni"},{"b":"4.1","h":"6.26","c":"الذَّكَرَ","d":"َrَkَّhdlٱ","e":"l-dhakara"},{"b":"4.8","h":"7.25","c":"وَالْأُنْثَى","d":"ٰàَhtnُaʾْlٱَw","e":"wal-unthā"}],"a":{"g":"And that He creates the two mates - the male and female -"}},"46":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.7","c":"مِنْ","d":"nِm","e":"min"},{"b":"0.99","h":"1.82","c":"نُطْفَةٍ","d":"ٍẗَfْṭُّn","e":"nuṭ'fatin"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.4","c":"إِذَا","d":"āَhdِiʾ","e":"idhā"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.41","c":"تُمْنَى","d":"ٰàَnْmُt","e":"tum'nā"}],"a":{"g":"From a sperm-drop when it is emitted"}},"47":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.06","c":"وَأَنَّ","d":"َّnَaʾَw","e":"wa-anna"},{"b":"1.2","h":"1.42","c":"عَلَيْهِ","d":"ِhْyَlَʿع","e":"ʿalayhi"},{"b":"2.3","h":"2.85","c":"النَّشْأَةَ","d":"َẗَaʾْhsَّnlٱ","e":"l-nashata"},{"b":"4.0","h":"4.73","c":"الْأُخْرَى","d":"ٰàَrْhkُaʾْlٱ","e":"l-ukh'rā"}],"a":{"g":"And that [incumbent] upon Him is the next creation"}},"48":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1.15","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"ۥُhَّnَaʾَw","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.27","c":"هُوَ","d":"َwُh","e":"huwa"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.97","c":"أَغْنَى","d":"ٰàَnْغَaʾ","e":"aghnā"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.41","c":"وَأَقْنَى","d":"ٰàَnْqَaʾَw","e":"wa-aqnā"}],"a":{"g":"And that it is He who enriches and suffices"}},"49":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"ۥُhَّnَaʾَw","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"1.7","h":"2.75","c":"هُوَ","d":"َwُh","e":"huwa"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.48","c":"رَبُّ","d":"ُّbَr","e":"rabbu"},{"b":"2.8","h":"4.55","c":"الشِّعْرَى","d":"ٰàَrْʿعِّhslٱ","e":"l-shiʿ'rā"}],"a":{"g":"And that it is He who is the Lord of Sirius"}},"50":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.55","c":"وَأَنَّهُ","d":"ٓۥُhَّnَaʾَw","e":"wa-annahu"},{"b":"2.9","h":"3.62","c":"أَهْلَكَ","d":"َkَlْhَaʾ","e":"ahlaka"},{"b":"3.7","h":"4.87","c":"عَادًا","d":"āًdāَʿع","e":"ʿādan"},{"b":"4.5","h":"6.37","c":"الْأُولَى","d":"ٰàَlwُaʾْlٱ","e":"l-ūlā"}],"a":{"g":"And that He destroyed the first [people of] 'Aad"}},"51":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"وَثَمُودَ","d":"۟āَdwُmَhtَw","e":"wathamūdā"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.46","c":"فَمَا","d":"ٓāَmَf","e":"famā"},{"b":"3.4","h":"4.64","c":"أَبْقَى","d":"ٰàَqْbَaʾ","e":"abqā"}],"a":{"g":"And Thamud - and He did not spare [them] -"}},"52":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.69","c":"وَقَوْمَ","d":"َmْwَqَw","e":"waqawma"},{"b":"0.85","h":"1.95","c":"نُوحٍ","d":"ٍḥwُn","e":"nūḥin"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.14","c":"مِنْ","d":"nِّm","e":"min"},{"b":"3.7","h":"5.23","c":"قَبْلُ","d":"ُlْbَq","e":"qablu"},{"b":"4.7","h":"7.8","c":"إِنَّهُمْ","d":"ْmُhَّnِiʾ","e":"innahum"},{"b":"6.6","h":"9.69","c":"كَانُوا","d":"۟āwُnāَk","e":"kānū"},{"b":"7.5","h":"11.2","c":"هُمْ","d":"ْmُh","e":"hum"},{"b":"8.0","h":"11.95","c":"أَظْلَمَ","d":"َmَlْẓَaʾ","e":"aẓlama"},{"b":"8.9","h":"13.41","c":"وَأَطْغَى","d":"ٰàَغْṭَaʾَw","e":"wa-aṭghā"}],"a":{"g":"And the people of Noah before. Indeed, it was they who were [even] more unjust and oppressing."}},"53":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.9","c":"وَالْمُؤْتَفِكَةَ","d":"َẗَkِfَtْwʾُmْlٱَw","e":"wal-mu'tafikata"},{"b":"1.8","h":"3.54","c":"أَهْوَى","d":"ٰàَwْhَaʾ","e":"ahwā"}],"a":{"g":"And the overturned towns He hurled down"}},"54":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.8","c":"فَغَشَّاهَا","d":"āَhٰàَّhsَغَf","e":"faghashāhā"},{"b":"1.5","h":"3.31","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"mā"},{"b":"1.9","h":"4.14","c":"غَشَّى","d":"ٰàَّhsَغ","e":"ghashā"}],"a":{"g":"And covered them by that which He covered."}},"55":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.7","c":"فَبِأَيِّ","d":"ِّàَaʾِbَf","e":"fabi-ayyi"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.3","c":"ءَالَاءِ","d":"ِءٓāَlāَء","e":"ālāi"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.19","c":"رَبِّكَ","d":"َkِّbَr","e":"rabbika"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.88","c":"تَتَمَارَى","d":"ٰàَrāَmَtَt","e":"tatamārā"}],"a":{"g":"Then which of the favors of your Lord do you doubt?"}},"56":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"هَذَا","d":"āَhdَٰh","e":"hādhā"},{"b":"0.9","h":"2.34","c":"نَذِيرٌ","d":"ٌryِhdَn","e":"nadhīrun"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.54","c":"مِنَ","d":"َnِّm","e":"mina"},{"b":"3.6","h":"5.1","c":"النُّذُرِ","d":"ِrُhdُّnlٱ","e":"l-nudhuri"},{"b":"4.7","h":"6.79","c":"الْأُولَى","d":"ٰٓàَlwُaʾْlٱ","e":"l-ūlā"}],"a":{"g":"This [Prophet] is a warner like the former warners."}},"57":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.65","c":"أَزِفَتِ","d":"ِtَfِzَaʾ","e":"azifati"},{"b":"0.85","h":"2","c":"الْءَازِفَةُ","d":"ُẗَfِzāَءْlٱ","e":"l-āzifatu"}],"a":{"g":"The Approaching Day has approached."}},"58":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.95","c":"لَيْسَ","d":"َsْyَl","e":"laysa"},{"b":"0.69","h":"1.95","c":"لَهَا","d":"āَhَl","e":"lahā"},{"b":"1.3","h":"3.06","c":"مِنْ","d":"nِm","e":"min"},{"b":"2.6","h":"4.14","c":"دُونِ","d":"ِnwُd","e":"dūni"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.28","c":"اللَّهِ","d":"ِhَّllٱ","e":"l-lahi"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.67","c":"كَاشِفَةٌ","d":"ٌẗَfِhsāَk","e":"kāshifatun"}],"a":{"g":"Of it, [from those] besides Allah, there is no remover."}},"59":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1.05","c":"أَفَمِنْ","d":"ْnِmَfَaʾ","e":"afamin"},{"b":"0.8","h":"2.18","c":"هَذَا","d":"āَhdَٰh","e":"hādhā"},{"b":"1.5","h":"3.37","c":"الْحَدِيثِ","d":"ِhtyِdَḥْlٱ","e":"l-ḥadīthi"},{"b":"2.6","h":"5.07","c":"تَعْجَبُونَ","d":"َnwُbَjgْʿعَt","e":"taʿjabūna"}],"a":{"g":"Then at this statement do you wonder?","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال عز وجل: ﴿ أفمن هذا الحديث تعجبون وتضحكون ولا تبكون وأنتم سامدون ﴾ {} بل أقول كل ما ورد في فضل البكاء من خشية الله فهو إظهار لفضيلة الخشية فإن البكاء ثمرة الخشية فقد قال تعالى: ﴿ فليضحكوا قليلا وليبكوا كثيرا ﴾ {} وقال تعالى: ﴿ يبكون ويزيدهم خشوعا ﴾ {} وقال عز وجل: ﴿ أفمن هذا الحديث تعجبون وتضحكون ولا تبكون وأنتم سامدون ﴾ {}\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, do you then wonder at this discourse [hadith], and laugh and do not weep, while you amuse yourselves [samidun]?\n\nRather, I say: All that has come regarding the virtue of weeping from fear of Allah [khashya] is a manifestation of the virtue of fear [khashya], for weeping is the fruit of fear [khashya]. Indeed, He, the Exalted, has said: \"So let them laugh a little and weep much.\" And He, the Exalted, has said: \"They weep, and it increases them in humility [khushu'].\" And He, the Mighty and Majestic, has said: \"Indeed, do you then wonder at this discourse [hadith], and laugh and do not weep, while you amuse yourselves [samidun]?\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"60":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.9","c":"وَتَضْحَكُونَ","d":"َnwُkَḥْḍَtَw","e":"wataḍḥakūna"},{"b":"1.6","h":"3.32","c":"وَلَا","d":"āَlَw","e":"walā"},{"b":"2.2","h":"4.41","c":"تَبْكُونَ","d":"َnwُkْbَt","e":"tabkūna"}],"a":{"g":"And you laugh and do not weep"}},"61":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"وَأَنْتُمْ","d":"ْmُtnَaʾَw","e":"wa-antum"},{"b":"2.0","h":"2.44","c":"سَامِدُونَ","d":"َnwُdِmَٰs","e":"sāmidūna"}],"a":{"g":"While you are proudly sporting?"}},"62":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.9","c":"فَاسْجُدُوا","d":"۟āwُdُjgْsٱَf","e":"fa-us'judū"},{"b":"1.1","h":"2.61","c":"لِلَّهِ","d":"ِhَّlِl","e":"lillahi"},{"b":"2.4","h":"4.38","c":"وَاعْبُدُوا","d":"۟āwُdُbْʿعٱَw","e":"wa-uʿ'budū"}],"a":{"g":"So prostrate to Allah and worship [Him]."}}}